manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Specifically designed for pressure demanding applications such as CPU or radiator cooling, the classic NF-P12 is a long-standing favourite among enthusiast users around the world and helped to found Noctua’s reputation as a top-tier manufacturer of premium quality quiet cooling components. The new redux edition reissues this award-winning model in a streamlined, accessibly priced package that has been reduced to the essential core: the NF-P12 premium fan. Its industry grade SSO bearing and over 150.000 hours MTTF rating make the NF-P12 redux a proven premium choice that provides trusted Noctua quality. The 1300rpm PWM version features Noctua’s proprietary NE-FD1 PWM IC for automatic speed control, which allows to strike a perfect balance between high cooling capacity and low noise operation in each given situation.

Proven NF-P12 design Tens of thousands of quiet cooling enthusiasts around the globe swear by Noctua's classic NF-P12. Thanks to its impressive quietness, excellent performance and impeccable quality, the NF-P12 has become an established reference for quiet 120mm fans.

Pressure-optimised Nine-Blade Design Specifically developed for high-impedance applications such as CPU coolers, water-cooling radiators or cases with tight fan grills, the NF-P12's nine-blade impeller provides outstanding pressure and airflow performance. SSO-Bearing Combining the proven concept of hydrodynamic bearing with an additional magnet that supports the self-stabilisation of the rotor axis, Noctua's time-tested technology has become synonymous with supremely quiet operation and exceptional long-term stability. Vortex-Control Notches Noctua's signature Vortex-Control Notches split up trailing edge vortices and thus spread the fan's noise emission over a wider range of frequencies. This measure makes the fan sound more pleasant to the human ear. Colour-customisable with NA-SAVP1 anti-vibration pads The fan’s frame can be outfitted with Noctua’s chromax line NA-SAVP1 anti-vibration pads. Available in black, red, blue, white, green and yellow, these pads not only damp minute vibrations but also allow the fan to be colour-customised in order to coordinate it with popular build colour schemes!

Streamlined Redux Edition The redux product line reissues some of Noctua's most popular, award-winning models by presenting them in streamlined, accessibly priced packages. All redux edition products are industry proven, time-tested models that helped to found Noctua's reputation as a first-tier supplier of premium grade low noise cooling equipment.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 5, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Silent, Solid, Huge upgrade to case fans at decent price.
reviews.reviewText: This is the budget series so I wasn’t sure what to expect but they’re great. I was actually amazed at how much quieter my case got after I replaced all the OEM fans with these.If you don’t need all the adapters and you’re OK with a tiny performance loss compared to the normal series, these are fantastic.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Can not hear them running.
reviews.reviewText: This reviewer recently finished his first computer build. The computer was built for home use and some digital image manipulation. It is not used for gaming. It neither needs, nor has, liquid CPU cooling.The case in which the computer was assembled came with two three-wire, fans installed. These fans were selected to upgrade to a 4-wire, PWM, fan.Installation was easier than easy and the direction of the airflow was clearly marked on the frame of the fan. The marking of the direction of flow was a nice assist for a first-time computer builder.In use the fans are completely silent and are readily controlled in BIOS. The computer never runs hot, the fans never run at max RPM, so the fans are apparently more than adequate for this build.They are not lighted, but the case has no transparent or translucent surfaces. Lighted fans spark no interest at any rate!In conclusion, these fans were a nice upgrade...noticeably more robust than the originals...for this build. The fans were a totally satisfactory purchase.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great Quality and Low Noise Level
reviews.reviewText: The fan was easy to install and feel nice. You can tell that they are were made with user experience in mind.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Quiet and Reliable Case Fan That Moves a Decent Amount of Air
reviews.reviewText: Converted a water-cooled system to an air-cooled one and used four fans and ducting to wash air over the front of a Thermaltake P5 case. I can feel the air movement even if I can't see it. They aren't quite as quiet as the water-cooled system, but I don't have to change their coolant. They are a win for me.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Amazingly quiet. Pushes plenty of air.
reviews.reviewText: After building a new PC, I noticed that one of the older Case fans, I reused, was making more noise than I was willing deal with, every time system load was high.Replaced that (ball bearing) fan with this one. What a difference! Same amount of air. Zero noise unless it's on Max power. Plus no more ugly brown plastic colors.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 10, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Really quiet at 900 RPM
reviews.reviewText: I installed it as a case fan in my Antec build. The fan is silently quiet at 900 RPM when my PC is idle or light load, while I do can hear slight humming under my desk at 1300 RPM when my PC is under stress. The 1300 RPM humming is not bad though, but it shows its pale when compared to my other fans in the same build: Antec 3-speed case fans and Noctua CPU sink fan (yes same brand probably even same model ironically) which has no humming and also run at 1300 RPM. I think it might be individual parts difference. so I kept this purchase hoping this fan will stay at 900 RPM load mostly.Installation difficulty is moderate, because it was a replacement in a cramp space of the existing build. I didn't install anti-vibrating corner pads which would be a separate purchase shipment. I didn't know such pad thing exists for Redux mode until after. There are no review says it makes too much difference besides cosmetic so I am lazy to reopen the case for now.I believe in Noctua. The above the another Noctua CPU sink fan has been running ten years 24/7 (yes you read it correct) and still quiet at 1300 RPM. I am convinced.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 23, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These things aren't effing around when it comes to quiet
reviews.reviewText: I built a new PC when my old motherboard died, and I installed these as an upgrade to my old, dusty fans. "Dusty Fans," by the way, is the name of my favorite stripper at the Silvermuff Cougar Club, which I admit is a bit niche, but if you like that sort of thing, Dusty Fans will give you the lapdance to end all lapdances that leave you confused about your feelings toward women your mother's age. She's got a bit of a tricky hip, so her straddle isn't what it used to be, but like the fans in my PC, she keeps it cool and dry and very, very quiet.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I use these to pull heat away from my 240 mm aio loaded with two Corsair fans in push config. These make 0 noise and helped lower my temps even more. Well worth the money and if I didn’t run rgb I would use these for every fan spot.
Como siempre un excelente producto, calidad, precio, bajo consumo, silencioso.Me ayudó a mejorar el flujo de aire de un gabinete Asus prime AP201.

O produto funciona como o desejado, comprei sabendo que o rpm dele é um pouco baixo pois vou utilizar apenas como exaustor traseiro do gabinete. Mas um DETALHE me deixou desapontado, ele faz um minino de barulho que poderia ser reduzido com a aplicação de borrachas na parte que entra em contato com o gabinete. Pela faixa de preço ele deveria vir com isso já de fábrica

reviews.reviewText: Simply the best fans for silent PCs. This one is completely silent, and my i5-12400F idles at 36C. Have a few Noctuas, a few of them running for over 10 years - silently and flawlessly.This is the most basic model, but still would be nice to have silicone corner inserts.
